# Requirement

Source task: `1daycloud`

The generated interface should implement the following Vision2Web Level 2 frontend requirement.

I want to build a OneDay Cloud website. When someone opens the site, they arrive at the homepage which serves as the main entry point to all the platform's services and products. The homepage has a navigation menu at the top that provides access to different sections of the website.

From the homepage, if I click on the "App Store" option in the navigation menu, it takes me to the App Store page. Within the App Store, I can access different applications including OneClick App and the Digital Business Card Directory. The OneClick App page showcases a service where users can select an existing application from OneDay App Store or create their own, with options to enter mobile number and send OTP code. The Digital Business Card Directory page presents a digital business card solution where users can create their digital business card and share it through a searchable directory of business cards.

If I go back to the homepage and click on "Services" in the navigation menu, I'm taken to the Services page. This page provides an overview of all the services that OneDay Cloud offers. It includes service descriptions, pricing information if applicable, and details about what OneDay Cloud can provide to its customers, such as App Store 1Store, Smart Application Designer SMA, and Ready Backend Design & Hosting for API Developers.

From the homepage, I can also access the Learning Hub page by clicking on "Learning Hub" in the navigation menu. This takes me to the OneDay Academy page, which appears to be an educational resource or training platform where users can learn about OneDay Cloud's products, cloud technologies, or related topics. The page includes various courses and workshops such as "Learn The Dashboard From A To Z", "No Code Apps in Dashboard", "No-Code Workshops", "Website & App Builder", "OneDay AI Apps", "Webinar & Demo", "App Builder Workshop", and "Oneday Apps", each with a "Start Now" button to begin the learning experience.

The homepage navigation also includes a "Company" option. When I click on it, I'm directed to the Company page, which likely provides information about OneDay Cloud as an organization, including company background, mission, vision, and other corporate information.

If I need to get in touch with OneDay Cloud, I can click on the "Contact" link in the navigation menu from the homepage. This takes me to the Contact page, where I can find contact information including address (2393 Ulaya, Ulaya District, 7235 Riyadh 12244, Saudi Arabia), phone & WhatsApp (00966114868394), email (info@1daycloud.com), website (1daycloud.com), and bank account details. The page also includes a contact form where users can submit their full name, email, mobile number, subject, and message.

Each of these pages maintains the same navigation menu structure, so from any page, I can easily navigate to any other section by clicking the appropriate menu item. This allows me to explore the App Store (which includes OneClick App and Digital Business Card Directory), review the Services offered, access learning materials in the Learning Hub (OneDay Academy), learn about the Company, or reach out through the Contact page, all while being able to return to the homepage at any time by clicking the OneDay Cloud logo or home link.


